{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, DR2new can only provide lower limits on the characteristic scale and amplitude of the monochromatic model: log 10 (k *,0.05 /Mpc -1) = 7.6 and log 10 A 0.05 ζ = -1.7 meaning that a whole range of models predicting Dirac-delta power spectrum can equally good describe the signal of DR2new.",
    "This behaviour is explained in the left panel of Fig. 19, for which we have simulated GWB signal generated by the monochromatic primordial scalar perturbations, Eq.",
    "(26), and attempted to recover a more general power law model of the form S (f) ∼ f -γ used in Paper III to model an arbitrary common red noise process.",
    "After a rapid decrease, the recovered slope stabilises at γ ∼ 3.5 in the limit of large k *, and becomes consistent with both values obtained with DR2new and the theoretically predicted 13/3 for the background from circular, GW-driven SMBHBs.",
    "This degeneracy can raise important issues when one tries to disentangle one signal from another."
  ]
}